  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <note>
      <para>
        The package source is distributed in <filename
        class="extension">.zip</filename> format and requires
        <command>unzip</command>, but it has been correctly packaged and will
        create the jasper-&jasper-version; directory when you unzip it.
      </para>
    </note>

    <para>
      Install JasPer by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>patch -Np1 -i ../jasper-&jasper-version;-security_fixes-1.patch &amp;&amp;
./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --mandir=/usr/share/man \
            --disable-static \
            --enable-shared &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

